<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-204-245 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 512 704</DOCID><JOURNAL>Soft-Letter  March 7 1991 v8 n13 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT The Mercury Group 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Postscript. (Soft-Letter adds new personnel to handle growingpublishing and conference operations and related products)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tarter, Jeffrey.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>POSTSCRIPT: Over the past year, our modest newsletter venture has turned intoa somewhat more complicated business.andP;  We now produce two newslettersSoft*letter and SLC, our monthly classified publication), three conferences(OpCon East and West, and now GeoCon), and a bunch of ancillary products(data disks, mailing lists, electronic editions, etc.).andP;  To keep track ofthis activity, we've added several new people whose voices you'll probablyencounter on the phone.andP;  Soft*letter now has two circulation managers--JimGilsenan (mornings) and Marni Hatfield (afternoons).andP;  Barbara Drainonihandles advertising for SLC and acts as our conference registrar.andP;  And HilaryWhite, our new bookkeeper, keeps track of money and government paperwork (inabout equal quantities).andM;Also, marketing director Tom Stitt has a new title: He's now associatepublisher, which probably means we'll have to buy him a new box of businesscards.andP;  Ah, the burdens of growth.andO;</TEXT></DOC>